<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In <a title="Binding and Finishing" href="Binding_and_Finishing">binding and finishing</a>, a <a title="Perforation" href="Perforation">perforation</a> made parallel to the <a title="Spine" href="Spine">spine</a> of a <a title="Jaw Fold" href="Jaw_Fold">jaw fold</a> in <a title="Signature" href="Signature">signature</a>s produced for school workbooks. The perforation allows answer sections to be removed and passed in (or eaten by the student's dog, as the case may be), leaving the questions bound in the book. 
</p>
